Getting Started

Prerequisites

- Node.js and npm installed on your machine
- [OpenAI API Key] (for AI-powered language model functionality)

Installation

1. Clone the repository:

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/sagebot.git
   ```

2. Install dependencies:

   ```bash
   cd sagebot
   npm install
   ```    

3. Set up your OpenAI API Key SERPAPI API Key by creating a `.env` file in the project root:

   ```plaintext
   OPENAI_API_KEY="your-api-key-here"
   SERPAPI_API_KEY ="your serpapi-key"
   ```
4 run the testAgent to see how llm can be limited to get data from a particular end point(www.stackoverflow.com):

    ```bash
   node tesAgent
   ```

5. Start the server:

   ```bash
   npm start
   ```

6. Open the application in your browser: [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000)

7. Due to upload issues the  retrival augment generator notebook can be found at:
https://github.com/A-l-Mahi/sageBot/blob/main/notebook.ipynb

Usage

 Creating Projects and Files

- Click "New Project" to create a new project.
- Click "New File" to create a new file within a project.
- Enter project and file names in the respective input fields.

Editing Code

- The code editor is in the "Editor" section.
- Click on a file in the file manager to load its content into the editor.
- Use the "Save," "Copy," and "Debug" buttons for file actions.

Chatting with Docs

- Use the chat input area to write messages.
- Attach files by using the file upload feature.
- Click "Send" to send your message to the server and receive responses.

Features

- Create and manage projects and files.
- Edit code in a user-friendly editor.
- Chat with AI for code debugging and generation.
- File upload for retrival augmented generation.

